{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T09:09:46.448Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Load balancing across agent pools"},{"type":"text","text":" is the strategy of distributing incoming requests across multiple groups (pools) of agent workers so each pool handles the right kind of work, latency stays low under load, and failures in one pool don’t collapse the whole system. In a distributed multi-agent swarm, you typically have several pools (e.g., orchestrator pool, specialist pools, region-specific pools), and the load balancer decides which pool—and which worker in that pool—should process each request."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"agent pool"},{"type":"text","text":" is a group of identical worker replicas that share:\n- The same agent logic (e.g., orchestrator, scraper, code-generator).\n- The same resources (CPU, memory, model access).\n- The same boundaries (e.g., region, tenant, domain)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Load balancing"},{"type":"text","text":" is the mechanism that:\n- Routes requests to the right pool.\n- Picks a worker within that pool.\n- Handles failures (retries, fallbacks).\n- Adapts to load (e.g., auto-scales pools)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of it like a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"restaurant with multiple kitchens"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Kitchen A: Handles appetizers.\n- Kitchen B: Handles mains.\n- Kitchen C: Handles desserts.\n- The "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"host"},{"type":"text","text":" (load balancer) routes each order to the right kitchen."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why it matters"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Without load balancing, you have:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Single point of failure"},{"type":"text","text":": One worker handles all requests; if it fails, the system is down.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Latency spikes"},{"type":"text","text":": One worker gets overloaded; others idle.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Poor fault tolerance"},{"type":"text","text":": If one pool fails, the whole system is affected."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"With load balancing, you get:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"High availability"},{"type":"text","text":": Requests are routed to healthy workers.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Low latency"},{"type":"text","text":": Requests go to the least-busy worker.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fault isolation"},{"type":"text","text":": If one pool fails, others can handle overflow."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of load balancing as a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"traffic controller"},{"type":"text","text":" for agent pools:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pools"},{"type":"text","text":": Different “airports” (e.g., orchestrator pool, scraper pool).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Workers"},{"type":"text","text":": Individual “planes” at each airport.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Load balancer"},{"type":"text","text":": The traffic controller that assigns incoming flights to the right airport and plane."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The controller decides:\n- Which airport to use (e.g., orchestrator vs. scraper).\n- Which plane to use (e.g., least-busy worker).\n- If a plane is broken, reroute to another."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How it works"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Pool selection: Which pool handles the request?"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Domain-based routing"},{"type":"text","text":": Route based on the task domain.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"domain=scrape"},{"type":"text","text":" → scraper pool.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"domain=code"},{"type":"text","text":" → code-generator pool.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"domain=orchestrate"},{"type":"text","text":" → orchestrator pool."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"def select_pool(task: dict):\n    if task[\"domain\"] == \"scrape\":\n        return \"scraper_pool\"\n    elif task[\"domain\"] == \"code\":\n        return \"code_pool\"\n    else:\n        return \"orchestrator_pool\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Tenant-based routing"},{"type":"text","text":": Route based on the tenant (e.g., user ID, organization).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"tenant_id=123"},{"type":"text","text":" → pool for tenant 123.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"tenant_id=456"},{"type":"text","text":" → pool for tenant 456."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This isolates tenants (e.g., for compliance, data residency)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Region-based routing"},{"type":"text","text":": Route based on the user’s region.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"region=us-east"},{"type":"text","text":" → US-east pool.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"region=eu-west"},{"type":"text","text":" → EU-west pool."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This minimizes latency and meets data residency requirements."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. Worker selection: Which worker in the pool handles the request?"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Round-robin"},{"type":"text","text":": Distribute requests evenly across workers.\n- Worker 1 → Worker 2 → Worker 3 → Worker 1 →..."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Least-connections"},{"type":"text","text":": Route to the worker with the fewest active connections.\n- Worker 1: 10 connections.\n- Worker 2: 5 connections.\n- Worker 3: 15 connections.\n- Route to Worker 2."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Weighted round-robin"},{"type":"text","text":": Assign weights based on capacity.\n- Worker 1: weight=1 (1 CPU).\n- Worker 2: weight=2 (2 CPUs).\n- Worker 3: weight=1 (1 CPU).\n- Route 1:2:1 to workers."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Sticky routing"},{"type":"text","text":": Preserve session state by routing to the same worker.\n- User 123 → Worker 2 (always)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This helps with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"prompt caching"},{"type":"text","text":" (reduces LLM costs), but requires state to be in-memory on that worker."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. Health checks and failure handling"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Health checks"},{"type":"text","text":": Periodically check if workers are healthy.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"GET /health"},{"type":"text","text":" → 200 OK.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"GET /health"},{"type":"text","text":" → 500 Error → mark unhealthy."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Failure handling"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Retry"},{"type":"text","text":": Retry on the same worker or a different one.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fallback"},{"type":"text","text":": Route to a fallback pool (e.g., simpler model).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Circuit breaker"},{"type":"text","text":": Stop routing to a failing pool."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"def route_request(task: dict):\n    pool = select_pool(task)\n    worker = select_worker(pool)\n    \n    if not is_healthy(worker):\n        worker = select_healthy_worker(pool)\n        if not worker:\n            return fallback(task)  # fallback pool\n    \n    return send_to_worker(worker, task)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Architecture"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A typical load-balanced agent pool stack:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  User Requests                                      │\n│  ↓                                                  │\n│  Load Balancer (ALB, Kubernetes Service, HAProxy) │\n│  ↓                                                  │\n│  ┌────────────────┐  ┌────────────────┐            │\n│  │ Orchestrator   │  │ Specialist     │            │\n│  │ Pool           │  │ Pool (Scraper) │            │\n│  │ Worker 1..N    │  │ Worker 1..N    │            │\n│  └────────────────┘  └────────────────┘            │\n│       ↓                    ↓                        │\n│  Task Queue (Redis, Kafka)                          │\n│       ↓                    ↓                        │\n│  LLM (Claude) + Tools                              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The load balancer routes to the right pool, then to the right worker."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation patterns"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Kubernetes Service (round-robin)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"apiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: orchestrator-svc\nspec:\n  selector:\n    app: orchestrator\n  ports:\n    - port: 80\n      targetPort: 8000\n  type: ClusterIP"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This creates a Kubernetes Service that routes to all "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"orchestrator"},{"type":"text","text":" pods (round-robin)."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"HAProxy (weighted round-robin)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"haproxy"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# haproxy.cfg\nbackend orchestrator_pool\n    balance roundrobin\n    option httpchk GET /health\n    server worker1 orchestrator-1:8000 weight 1 check\n    server worker2 orchestrator-2:8000 weight 2 check\n    server worker3 orchestrator-3:8000 weight 1 check"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This configures HAProxy with weighted round-robin (worker 2 has double capacity)."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom Python load balancer (least-connections)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"import httpx\nfrom collections import defaultdict\n\nworkers = [\n    {\"url\": \"http://orchestrator-1:8000\", \"connections\": 0},\n    {\"url\": \"http://orchestrator-2:8000\", \"connections\": 0},\n    {\"url\": \"http://orchestrator-3:8000\", \"connections\": 0},\n]\n\ndef select_worker_least_connections():\n    return min(workers, key=lambda w: w[\"connections\"])\n\nasync def route_request(task: dict):\n    worker = select_worker_least_connections()\n    worker[\"connections\"] += 1\n    \n    try:\n        response = await httpx.post(worker[\"url\"], json=task)\n        return response.json()\n    finally:\n        worker[\"connections\"] -= 1"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This routes to the least-busy worker."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Benefits"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"High availability"},{"type":"text","text":": Requests are routed to healthy workers."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Low latency"},{"type":"text","text":": Requests go to the least-busy worker."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fault isolation"},{"type":"text","text":": If one pool fails, others can handle overflow."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Cost efficiency"},{"type":"text","text":": Scale pools independently based on demand."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Trade-offs"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Aligns with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"modern cloud infrastructure"},{"type":"text","text":" (Kubernetes, serverless, HAProxy).\n- Handles "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"bursty traffic"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., spikes at 9 AM).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Independent scaling"},{"type":"text","text":": Pools scale independently."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Trade-offs:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Adds complexity"},{"type":"text","text":": Load balancer, health checks, failure handling.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Monitoring overhead"},{"type":"text","text":": Track pool utilization, latency, errors.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Sticky routing requires in-memory state"},{"type":"text","text":": Limits scaling unless externalized."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best practices"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use domain-based routing"},{"type":"text","text":" to route tasks to the right pool."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use least-connections"},{"type":"text","text":" for worker selection (balances load)."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Set up health checks"},{"type":"text","text":" to detect unhealthy workers."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use circuit breakers"},{"type":"text","text":" to stop routing to failing pools."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Monitor pool utilization"},{"type":"text","text":" to know when to scale."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Load balancing = "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"distributing requests across agent pools"},{"type":"text","text":" so each pool handles the right work."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pool selection"},{"type":"text","text":" (domain, tenant, region) routes to the right pool."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Worker selection"},{"type":"text","text":" (round-robin, least-connections, weighted) picks the right worker."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Health checks"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"failure handling"},{"type":"text","text":" ensure reliability."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This pattern is critical for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"high availability"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"low latency"},{"type":"text","text":" in distributed swarms."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph"}]}}
